<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1870-08-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1870-08-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="59" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d59">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">No. 59.</note>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Received 9.50 a. m., August 13,
                                1870.]</seg></opener>
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. E. B. Washburne</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr. Fish</persName>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1870-08-12"><hi rend="smallcaps">August 12, 1870.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Fish,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington:</hi></p>
                        <p>French government decides North Germans, with certain exceptions, quit
                            France. Advise Prussian government and instruct me. Impossible for great
                            numbers of poor to leave without pecuniary aid.</p>
                        <p>Will Prussian government place a credit at my disposition to assist poor
                            in leaving? It seems necessary in the interest of humanity.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WASHBURNE, <hi rend="italic">Paris.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>